            >>>>>>> TEXT CONTROL CODES <<<<<<<

08		BACKSPACE
0A		LINEFEED, CURSOR DOWN
0B		CURSOR 1 LINE UP
0C		CLEAR WINDOW
0D		CR, CURSOR TO LEFT EDGE
0E		SWITCH TO NORMAL DISPLAY (REVERSE 0F)
0F		SWITCH TO SPECIAL CHARACTERS
1B		ESCAPE


9B(N)40		INSERT N SPACES
9B(N)41		CURSOR UP N LINES
9B(N)42		CURSOR DOWN N LINES
9B(N)43		CURSOR RIGHT N CHARS
9B(N)44		CURSOR LEFT N CHARS
9B(N)45		CURSOR DOWN N LINES IN COLUMN 1
9B(N)46		CURSOR UP N LINES IN COLUMN 1
9B(N)(3B N)48	SET CURSOR IN LINE; COLUMN
9B 4A		CLEAR WINDOW AT CURSOR
9B 4B		CLEAR LINE AT CURSOR
9B 4C		INSERT LINE
9B 4D		DELETE LINE
9B(N)50		DELETE N CHARS AT CURSOR
9B(N)53		MOVE N LINES UP
9B(N)54		MOVE N LINES DOWN
9B 32 30 68	FROM NOW ON: LINEFEED => LINEFEED+RETURN
9B 32 30 6C	FROM NOW ON: LINEFEED => LINEFEED ONLY
9B 6E		SEND THE CURSOR POSITION. A STRING OF THE FOLLOWING
		FORM IS RETURNED: 9B (LINE) 3B(COLUMN) 52

9B(STYLE);(F COLOUR);(B COLOUR) 6D
The 3 parameters are decimal numbers in ascii format. they mean:

STYLE:		0=NORMAL
		1=BOLD
		3=ITALIC
		4=UNDERLINE
		7=INVERSE VIDIO
	
F COLOUR:	30-37: TEXT COLOUR 0-7
B COLOUR:	40-47: BACKGROUND COLOUR 0-7

9B (LENGTH) 74	SET MAXIMUM NUMBER OF DISPLAY LINES
9B (WIDTH) 75	SET MAXIMUM LINE LENGTH
9B (MARGIN) 78	DEFINE LEFT MARGIN IN PIXELS
9B (MARGIN) 79	DEFINES TOP MARGIN IN PIXELS

The last four functions can be used to return to the default
settings by omitting the parameters.

9B 30 20 70	MAKE CURSOR INVISIBLE
9B 20 70	MAKE CURSOR VISIBLE
9B 71		SEND WINDOW DIMENSIONS. A string of the following form
		is returned:
	
		9B 31 3B 31 3B (LINES) 3B (COLUMNS) 73
